I realize how easy it is to live in America, how difficult it would be for the Queen to fully do her duty in Fiji if she removed herself from the country and live here. I sometimes feel bad for her, but there is nothing she can do to change her situation.

— Jared Feliciano, MS6

Overall, the celebrations in Fiji did mark a benchmark in the journey of our own political history. I think the development of Fiji in the last 20 years, more specifically in the last 10, can essentially be attributed to the growth of the multi-cultural Fijian Melanesian society. For the first time in history, Fiji is well suited to sustain itself and break away from its post-colonial debt cycle.

— Gareth Sharma, MS10
